about.summary: Chemical information from around the web. This package interacts with a suite of web services for chemical information. Sources include: Alan Wood's Compendium of Pesticide Common Names, Chemical Identifier Resolver, ChEBI, Chemical Translation Service, ChemIDplus, ChemSpider, ETOX, Flavornet, NIST Chemistry WebBook, OPSIN, PAN Pesticide Database, PubChem, SRS, Wikidata.

raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.1.1" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-webchem
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/webchem_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/webchem/webchem_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 614f178092650bd42f8713ddfc74ce7e42190b21d6d5846444a5ee90d8d7f160

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic

  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]

  host:
    - r-base
    - r-rcurl
    - r-data.tree
    - r-dplyr
    - r-httr
    - r-jsonlite
    - r-purrr
    - r-rvest
    - r-stringr
    - r-tibble
    - r-xml2

  run:
    - r-base
    - r-rcurl
    - r-data.tree
    - r-dplyr
    - r-httr
    - r-jsonlite
    - r-purrr
    - r-rvest
    - r-stringr
    - r-tibble
    - r-xml2

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('webchem')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('webchem')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://docs.ropensci.org/webchem, https://github.com/ropensci/webchem
  license: MIT
  summary: "Chemical information from around the web. This package interacts with a suite of web services for chemical information. Sources include: Alan Wood's Compendium of Pesticide Common Names, Chemical Identifier Resolver, ChEBI, Chemical Translation Service, ChemIDplus, ChemSpider, ETOX, Flavornet, NIST Chemistry\
    \ WebBook, OPSIN, PAN Pesticide Database, PubChem, SRS, Wikidata."

  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - mfakaehler
